        <heading>Payment of Wages and Other Compensation</heading>
        <section eId="sec_388_41">
          <num>388-41</num>
          <heading>Section 388-41</heading>
          <content>
            <p>[PART III]
[ยง388-41]ย Advance notice of termination of
employment.
If an employer requires an employee to give advance notice of
termination and the employee gives such notice, the employer shall be liable
for the wages which the employee would have earned during the stated period in
such notice starting from the day such notice is given, providing that the
employee does not voluntarily terminate the employment or the employment is not
terminated for cause prior to the last day of such period. [L 1972, c 52, pt of
ยง1]
